# FocusFlow v5

A gamified Pomodoro study tracker built with vanilla HTML/CSS/JS — a single-file application with no dependencies, no build step, and no backend.

## Contents

* What It Is
* Features
* Architecture
* Data Model
* Pages & Functionality
* Gamification
* Timer Modes
* Deployment
* LocalStorage & Persistence

---

# What It Is

FocusFlow is a personal study tracker featuring a Pomodoro timer, statistics dashboard, gamification system (XP, levels, achievements, coins, shop), and a virtual pet. The goal is simple: open the file, study, and track your progress.

**Live Demo:** https://kostasmour-cs.github.io/focusflow-v5/

---

# Features

| Category     | Details                                                                                             |
| ------------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Timer        | 7 modes (Sprint, Classic, Deep Work, Flow, Marathon, Custom, Free Run)                              |
| Subjects     | Unlimited subjects with custom colors, notes, and session history                                   |
| Dashboard    | KPI cards, weekly bar chart, calendar heatmap, weekly goals, motivational quotes                    |
| Analytics    | Pie chart, bar chart, trend line, hourly distribution, focus score progression                      |
| Achievements | 40+ achievements with XP rewards and unlock conditions                                              |
| Shop         | Achievement frames and profile badges purchasable with coins, including try-before-you-buy previews |
| Virtual Pet  | 3+ pets (Ghost, Cat, Dragon, etc.), energy/happiness/XP bars, daily quests, and boost system        |
| History      | Complete session history with subject filtering                                                     |
| Exams        | Exam schedule with countdown timers                                                                 |
| Streak       | Daily study streak with recovery option (cost: 10 coins)                                            |
| Journal      | Post-session notes and difficulty tracking                                                          |
| Language     | Greek UI                                                                                            |

---

# Architecture

```
focusflow_v5.html          ← Single-file application
├── <style>                 CSS variables, component styles, responsive layout
├── HTML pages              7 .page sections (timer, dashboard, subjects, history, ...)
├── <script>
│   ├── Constants           COLORS[], DAYS[], MODES[], ACHIEVEMENTS[], PET_MILESTONES[]
│   ├── Data (db)           Central application state persisted in localStorage
│   ├── Timer State (T)     Ephemeral runtime state (countdown, cycle, active session)
│   ├── Render Functions    renderDashboard(), renderSubjects(), renderShop(), ...
│   ├── Timer Engine        setInterval loop and phase transitions
│   ├── Gamification        earnXP(), earnCoins(), checkAchievements(), updateStreak()
│   └── Pet System          renderPet(), petBoost(), getPetDailyQuests(), ...
```

