# Gamification

## XP & Levels

XP earned per session:

```
XP = Session Duration (minutes) × 5
```

XP required to advance from Level N to N+1:

```
XP = 200 × 1.5^(N-1)
```

Examples:

| Level   | XP Required |
| ------- | ----------- |
| 1 → 2   | 200 XP      |
| 5 → 6   | ~1,013 XP   |
| 10 → 11 | ~7,689 XP   |

---

## Coins

Coins are earned through:

* Completed study sessions
* Streak milestones

Coins can be spent on:

* Shop purchases
* Streak recovery (10 coins)

---

## Streak System

* +1 day if you studied yesterday
* If exactly 1 day is missed:

  * Recovery option available for 10 coins
* If 2 or more days are missed:

  * Streak is permanently lost and resets to 1

---

## Achievements

Each achievement is defined using:

```js
check(stats) => Boolean
```

Achievements are automatically evaluated after every completed session through:

```js
checkAchievements()
```

---

# Timer Modes

| Mode         | Focus     | Break  | Cycles | Long Break |
| ------------ | --------- | ------ | ------ | ---------- |
| Sprint 🏃    | 20 min    | 5 min  | 4      | —          |
| Classic 🍅   | 25 min    | 5 min  | 4      | 15 min     |
| Deep Work 🧠 | 30 min    | 10 min | 3      | —          |
| Flow 🌊      | 60 min    | 20 min | 2      | —          |
| Marathon 🏁  | 90+ min   | 20 min | 2      | —          |
| Custom ⚙     | Custom    | Custom | Custom | —          |
| Free Run ∞   | Unlimited | —      | 1      | —          |

## Focus Score

Focus Score is calculated as:

```
(totalFocusTime / (maxCycles × focusSeconds)) × 100
```

The value is capped at 100%.

---

# Deployment

FocusFlow is a static HTML application and can be deployed anywhere.

```bash
# GitHub Pages
git add focusflow_v5.html
git commit -m "update"
git push origin main

# Result:
https://<username>.github.io/<repository>/focusflow_v5.html
```

No Node.js, npm, package manager, or build tool is required.

---

# LocalStorage & Persistence

| Key    | Description                                      |
| ------ | ------------------------------------------------ |
| ff3    | Main database object (current version)           |
| ff_db2 | Legacy key from v4, loaded if ff3 does not exist |
| ff_db  | Legacy key from v3, used as a fallback           |

The `load()` function checks all three keys in priority order to ensure backward compatibility with older saves.

## Reset All Data

Run the following command in the browser console:

```js
localStorage.removeItem('ff3')
```

This permanently removes all stored FocusFlow data.
